### RxDB CouchDB Replication Setup

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/rx-storage-dexie.md

Demonstrates the setup for replicating RxDB collections with a CouchDB backend. This involves importing necessary plugins, creating a database with Dexie storage, defining a collection schema, and initiating the replication. Dependencies: rxdb/plugins/replication-couchdb, rxdb/plugins/storage-dexie, rxdb/plugins/core.

```typescript
import { replicateCouchDB } from 'rxdb/plugins/replication-couchdb';
import { getRxStorageDexie } from 'rxdb/plugins/storage-dexie';
import { createRxDatabase } from 'rxdb/plugins/core';

// Create an RxDB Database with the Dexie Storage
const db = await createRxDatabase({
  name: 'mydb',
  storage: getRxStorageDexie()
});

// Add a Collection
await db.addCollections({
    humans: {
        schema: {
            version: 0,
            type: 'object',
            primaryKey: 'id',
            properties: {
                id: { type: 'string', maxLength: 100 },
                name: { type: 'string' },
                age: { type: 'number' }
              },
            required: ['id', 'name']
        }
    }
});

// Sync the Collection with a CouchDB Server
const replicationState = replicateCouchDB({
  replicationIdentifier: 'my-couchdb-replication',
  collection: db.humans,
  // The URL to your CouchDB endpoint
  url: 'http://example.com/db/humans'
});
```

